qas.question: Which Melbourne based university has campuses in Malaysia?
Which Melbourne based college has a research centre in Prato, Italy?
Which university is the second oldest in Australia?
What is the Group of Eight?

answers.text: a coalition of leading Australian tertiary institutions offering comprehensive and leading education

context: Melbourne universities have campuses all over Australia and some internationally. <a0_0>Swinburne University<a0_0/> has campuses in Malaysia, while <a1_0>Monash<a1_0/> has a research centre based in Prato, Italy. <a2_0>The University of Melbourne<a2_0/>, the second oldest university in Australia, was ranked first among Australian universities in the 2010 THES international rankings. The 2012–2013 Times Higher Education Supplement ranked the University of Melbourne as the 28th (30th by QS ranking) best university in the world. Monash University was ranked as the 99th (60th by QS ranking) best university in the world. Both universities are members of the Group of Eight, <a3_0>a coalition of leading Australian tertiary institutions offering comprehensive and leading education<a3_0/>.
